
                                            Experts say people need to live heather lives, this includes eating well and getting enough exercise.
                                         CAPE TOWN - The World Health Organisation has projected that diabetes  will be the seventh leading cause of death in the world in 2030. South Africans have been encouraged to get screened and tested for the chronic illness. Experts say people need to live heather lives, this includes eating well and getting enough exercise. Dr Muller Smit, a general practitioner in Cape Town, says more children are being diagnosed with type 2 diabetes. “We can see that type 1 diabetes is usually a younger patient who is lean in body weight whereas, in type 2, we can mostly see it in patients who are overweight.”